      "content": "Zyrtec (cetirizine) can help to alleviate some allergy symptoms, including nasal congestion and itching; however, it may not necessarily address the wheezing and throat tightness you're experiencing. It’s essential to differentiate between an allergic reaction and another respiratory issue. Even if allergies are the primary issue, using an inhaler to open airways might be necessary. Still, to ensure you're managing your symptoms appropriately and not overlooking anything potentially more serious, it would be best to consult with a healthcare provider. It's always better to be safe, especially when it comes to respiratory issues.",
